Stack is a Data Structure which works on the discipline LIFO (Last In First Out).
Recursion uses a system stack. Sometimes, to convert Recursion into iteration we have to use stacks. 
Some recursion are directly converted into interation and some uses stacks.

ADT of Stack:-

DATA:-
1. Space for storing elements. (because stacks is a collection of elements)
2. Top pointer. (a pointer pointing the topmost element)

OPERATIONS:-
1. push()
2. pop()
3. peek(index)
4. stackTop()
5. isEmpty()
6. isFull()